[Intro]

[Tyree]
Yo bro, i really need to talk to you about something man, man i see a lot of people changing around me man .. but you? You had to be the one aye

[Deach]
These dudes your hurting, why you hurting them? Like, i know who you are - your not like that. I know what's happening in your household .. do you want to talk about it or something?

[Sid]
And i'm not tryna like .. put all the blame on you. 'Cos I was the one who put us on TV, in the event that it'd try and change the hood. Not tryna glamorise it or nothing, just showing everybody what it's like out here .. and now its your turn to try and change it

[Verse 1]

[Sid]
I got my elbow on the window sill hand on my face looking out to the world. A lot of questions lay awake in my brain and I'm still trying to suss out what i'ma say, and if I do speak on somethings if it's you stone cup all that hates so here goes - why is it that when some guy makes it outta a hood life there like 'no we can't let ya' and allow five-o to rape girls and compensate them like they, the victim is so wrong and expect us working people to fund your wages for you to uphold the law which is what? exactly that I really need to know 'til then I'll stare outta my window
Hehe probably won't get an answer for that one

[Hook]

[Gin]
I got some questions in my mind that definitely need some answers right now cause I gotta know got all the pieces to the puzzle but can't seem to make it fit so I'm lost, tell me where to go

[Tyree]
But you turned your back and you went away, it's making me crazy I feel so alone why did you turn your back, why did you go away cause you were my brother, and you should of stayed

[Verse 2]

[Tyree]
